title: Appointments to the Hospital Authority
content_text:
p>
The Government announced today (November 30) the re-appointment of five members 
and appointment of two new members to the Hospital Authority (HA) with effect 
from December 1, 2007.  Dr Margaret Chung Wai-ling, Dr Anthony Ho Yiu-wah, Prof Thomas Wong Kwok-shing 
and Mr Paul Yu Shiu-tin are re-appointed for two years. Ms Polly Lau Mo-yee is 
re-appointed for one year, in line with past practice on the appointment of HA

re-appointed for one year, in line with past practice on the appointment of HA 
employees to the board. The new members are Mr Benjamin Hung Pi-cheng and Ms Yvonne Shing Mo-han. They 
are appointed for two years. Mr Hung is an experienced banker and is currently 
the head of Consumer Banking and Chief Executive Officer (Designate) of Standard 
Chartered Bank (Hong Kong) Limited. He is also a member of the Insurance 
Advisory Committee. Ms Shing is an accountant and is currently the National

Advisory Committee. Ms Shing is an accountant and is currently the National 
Chief Knowledge Officer and Partner of Deloitte Touche Tohmatsu. She has served 
as a member of the Commission on Strategic Development and the Central Policy 
Unit. Referring to the appointments, the Secretary for Food and Health, Dr York Chow, 
said: "I would like to thank the re-appointed members for their contribution to 
the HA Board and their advice to the Government on health services. I also 
welcome the two new members to the board. Their professional experience and

welcome the two new members to the board. Their professional experience and knowledge will be useful to the work of the board." With effect from December 1, 2007, the HA will comprise a chairman, 20 non-official members, three public officers and one principal officer from the HA.
